text: Birwadi is a census town in Raigad district in the state of Maharashtra, India. ==Demographics== India census, Birwadi had a population of 7271. Males constitute 54% of the population and females 46%. Birwadi has an average literacy rate of 75%, higher than the national average of 59.5%; with male literacy of 80% and female literacy of 68%. 16% of the population is under 6 years of age. ==References== Category:Cities and towns in Raigad district
title: Birwadi
